    "review-wip-reviewer-91979": {
      "status": "complete",
      "findings": 1,
      "findings_details": [
        {
          "file": "lib/runtime/orchestrator-runner-deadline.test.ts",
          "line": 83,
          "severity": "low",
          "category": "correctness",
          "title": "Deadline test uses hardcoded trusted: false instead of manifest.trusted",
          "body": "In runHangingTick (line 74-88), the inline sdkClient.run() call passes trusted: false unconditionally instead of manifest.trusted. The hanging-tick closure has access to manifest via its parameter, so this is a divergence from the pattern established in all other test fixtures (orchestrator-runner.test.ts:195-201 uses manifest.trusted, inflight-tick-registry.test.ts:159 uses the variable from scope). The consequence: if a future test calls runHangingTick with a trusted=true manifest, the assertion sdk.calls[0].trusted would get false and mislead the reviewer. More concretely, the plan (Task 3 acceptance criteria, line 358) states tests must verify trusted propagation by inspecting FakeAgentSdkClient.calls \u2014 this test does the opposite, hardcoding the field. The fix is to change trusted: false to trusted: manifest.trusted at line 83.",
          "confidence": "high"
        }
      ]
    },
